window.docContents[247].resolve({"/Basic-Types/Floating-Point-Numbers/#zh-basictypes-float-h001":{"contents":"Lean 没有专用的浮点文字。\n相反，浮点文字是通过 OfScientific 和 Neg 类型类的适当实例来解析的。\n\nFloating-Point Literals期限(-2.523 : Float)\n是语法糖(Neg.neg (OfScientific.ofScientific 22523 true 4) : Float)\n和术语(413.52 : Float32)\n是语法糖(OfScientific.ofScientific 41352 true 2 : Float32)\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009浮点数","header":"20.6.1. 句法","id":"/Basic-Types/Floating-Point-Numbers/#zh-basictypes-float-h001"},"/Basic-Types/Floating-Point-Numbers/#zh-basictypes-float-h010":{"contents":"Computes the natural logarithm ln x of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlog.\n\nComputes the natural logarithm ln x of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlogf.\n\nComputes the base-10 logarithm of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlog10.\n\nComputes the base-10 logarithm of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlog10f.\n\nComputes the base-2 logarithm of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlog2.\n\nComputes the base-2 logarithm of a floating-point number.This function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\nlog2f.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009浮点数\u0009API 参考","header":"20.6.2.6. 对数","id":"/Basic-Types/Floating-Point-Numbers/#zh-basictypes-float-h010"},"/Basic-Types/Linked-Lists/#list-syntax":{"contents":"列表文字写在方括号中，列表的元素用逗号分隔。\n将元素添加到列表前面的构造函数 List.cons 由中缀运算符 :: 表示。\n列表的语法既可以用在普通术语中，也可以用在模式中。\n\nList LiteralsThe syntax [a, b, c] is shorthand for a :: b :: c :: [], or\nList.cons a (List.cons b (List.cons c List.nil)). It allows conveniently constructing\nlist literals.For lists of length at least 64, an alternative desugaring strategy is used\nwhich uses let bindings as intermediates as in\nlet left := [d, e, f]; a :: b :: c :: left to avoid creating very deep expressions.\nNote that this changes the order of evaluation, although it should not be observable\nunless you use side effecting operations like dbg_trace.Conventions for notations in identifiers:* The recommended spelling of [] in identifiers is nil.* The recommended spelling of [a] in identifiers is singleton.\n\nList ConstructionThe list whose first element is head, where tail is the rest of the list.\nUsually written head :: tail.Conventions for notations in identifiers:* The recommended spelling of :: in identifiers is cons.\n\nConstructing Lists所有这些示例都是等效的：example : List Nat := [1, 2, 3]\nexample : List Nat := 1 :: [2, 3]\nexample : List Nat := 1 :: 2 :: [3]\nexample : List Nat := 1 :: 2 :: 3 :: []\nexample : List Nat := 1 :: 2 :: 3 :: .nil\nexample : List Nat := 1 :: 2 :: .cons 3 .nil\nexample : List Nat := .cons 1 (.cons 2 (.cons 3 .nil))\n\n\nPattern Matching and Lists所有这些功能都是等效的：def split : List α → List α × List α\n  | [] => ([], [])\n  | [x] => ([x], [])\n  | x :: x' :: xs =>\n    let (ys, zs) := split xs\n    (x :: ys, x' :: zs)\ndef split' : List α → List α × List α\n  | .nil => (.nil, .nil)\n  | x :: [] => (.singleton x, .nil)\n  | x :: x' :: xs =>\n    let (ys, zs) := split xs\n    (x :: ys, x' :: zs)\ndef split'' : List α → List α × List α\n  | .nil => (.nil, .nil)\n  | .cons x .nil => (.singleton x, .nil)\n  | .cons x (.cons x' xs) =>\n    let (ys, zs) := split xs\n    (.cons x ys, .cons x' zs)\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009链表","header":"20.15.1. 句法","id":"/Basic-Types/Linked-Lists/#list-syntax"},"/Basic-Types/Maps-and-Sets/#zh-basictypes-maps-treemap-h002":{"contents":"Returns the number of mappings present in the map.\n\nReturns true if the tree map contains no mappings.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009地图和套装\u0009基于树的地图","header":"20.19.8.2. 特性","id":"/Basic-Types/Maps-and-Sets/#zh-basictypes-maps-treemap-h002"},"/Basic-Types/Strings/#zh-basictypes-string-h019":{"contents":"Creates a new string that consists of the region of the input string delimited by the two positions.The result is \"\" if the start position is greater than or equal to the end position or if the\nstart position is at the end of the string. If either position is invalid (that is, if either points\nat the middle of a multi-byte UTF-8 character) then the result is unspecified.This is a legacy function. The recommended alternative is String.Pos.extract, but usually\nit is even better to operate on String.Slice instead and call String.Slice.copy (only) if\nrequired.Examples:* \"red green blue\".extract ⟨0⟩ ⟨3⟩ = \"red\"* \"red green blue\".extract ⟨3⟩ ⟨0⟩ = \"\"* \"red green blue\".extract ⟨0⟩ ⟨100⟩ = \"red green blue\"* \"red green blue\".extract ⟨4⟩ ⟨100⟩ = \"green blue\"* \"L∃∀N\".extract ⟨1⟩ ⟨2⟩ = \"∃∀N\"* \"L∃∀N\".extract ⟨2⟩ ⟨100⟩ = \"\"\n\nReturns the character at position p of a string. If p is not a valid position, returns the\nfallback value (default : Char), which is 'A', but does not panic.This function is overridden with an efficient implementation in runtime code. See\nString.Pos.Raw.utf8GetAux for the reference implementation.This is a legacy function. The recommended alternative is String.Pos.get, combined with\nString.pos or another means of obtaining a String.Pos.Examples:* \"abc\".get ⟨1⟩ = 'b'* \"abc\".get ⟨3⟩ = (default : Char) because byte 3 is at the end of the string.* \"L∃∀N\".get ⟨2⟩ = (default : Char) because byte 2 is in the middle of '∃'.\n\nReturns the character at position p of a string. Panics if p is not a valid position.See String.pos? and String.Pos.get for a safer alternative.This function is overridden with an efficient implementation in runtime code. See\nString.utf8GetAux for the reference implementation.This is a legacy function. The recommended alternative is String.Pos.get, combined with\nString.pos! or another means of obtaining a String.Pos.Examples* \"abc\".get! ⟨1⟩ = 'b'\n\nReturns the character at position p of a string. Returns (default : Char), which is 'A', if\np is not a valid position.Requires evidence, h, that p is within bounds instead of performing a run-time bounds check as\nin String.get.A typical pattern combines get' with a dependent if-expression to avoid the overhead of an\nadditional bounds check. For example:def getInBounds? (s : String) (p : String.Pos) : Option Char :=\n  if h : s.atEnd p then none else some (s.get' p h)\nEven with evidence of ¬ s.atEnd p, p may be invalid if a byte index points into the middle of a\nmulti-byte UTF-8 character. For example, \"L∃∀N\".get' ⟨2⟩ (by decide) = (default : Char).This is a legacy function. The recommended alternative is String.Pos.get, combined with\nString.pos or another means of obtaining a String.Pos.Examples:* \"abc\".get' 0 (by decide) = 'a'* let lean := \"L∃∀N\"; lean.get' (0 |> lean.next |> lean.next) (by decide) = '∀'\n\nReturns the character at position p of a string. If p is not a valid position, returns none.This function is overridden with an efficient implementation in runtime code. See\nString.utf8GetAux? for the reference implementation.This is a legacy function. The recommended alternative is String.Pos.get, combined with\nString.pos? or another means of obtaining a String.Pos.Examples:* \"abc\".get? ⟨1⟩ = some 'b'* \"abc\".get? ⟨3⟩ = none* \"L∃∀N\".get? ⟨1⟩ = some '∃'* \"L∃∀N\".get? ⟨2⟩ = none\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009弦乐\u0009API 参考\u0009原始头寸","header":"20.8.4.5.6. 字符串查找","id":"/Basic-Types/Strings/#zh-basictypes-string-h019"},"/Error-Explanations/About___-___dependsOnNoncomputable___/#zh-errorexplanations-dependsonnoncomputable-root":{"contents":"\n\n此错误表明指定的定义依赖于一个或多个不依赖于该定义的定义。\n包含可执行代码，因此需要标记为 noncomputable。这样的\n定义可以进行类型检查，但不包含可由 Lean 执行的代码。\n\n如果您希望错误消息中指定的定义不可计算，请将其标记为\nnoncomputable 将解决此错误。如果没有，请检查不可计算的\n它所依赖的定义：它们可能是不可计算的，因为它们无法编译，是\naxiom，或本身标记为 noncomputable。让你的一切\n定义的不可计算依赖项可计算也将解决此错误。参见手册\nsection on Modifiers for more information about noncomputable\n定义。\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009错误说明","header":"关于： dependsOnNoncomputable","id":"/Error-Explanations/About___-___dependsOnNoncomputable___/#zh-errorexplanations-dependsonnoncomputable-root"},"/ValidatingProofs/#zh-validatingproofs-h019":{"contents":"在可信环境中，编写定理陈述（“挑战”），然后将挑战以及提议的证明提供给 comparator 工具，并启用外部检查器，如其中所述。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009验证 Lean 证明\u0009黄金标准： comparator  和外部检查器","header":"指示","id":"/ValidatingProofs/#zh-validatingproofs-h019"},"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h002":{"contents":"#11637 声明模块系统不再是实验性的，并使 experimental.module 选项成为无操作。\n\n有关文档，请参阅参考手册中的 模块和可见性 部分。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.27.0 (2026-01-24)\u0009亮点","header":"模块系统稳定","id":"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h002"},"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h011":{"contents":"* grind ring 中的 BitVec 支持 (#11639)\n  和 grind lia (#11640);* 新配置选项 grind -reducible，允许扩展不可简化声明\n  在 定义等价 测试期间（#11480）；* 支持异构构造函数单射性（#11491）；* 支持 LawfulOfScientific 类 (#11331)；* grind策略块内的语法 use [ns Foo] 和 instantiate only [ns Foo]，\n  它具有激活所有范围内的研磨模式的效果\n  namespace (#11335);* 新的 grind_pattern 约束（#11405 和\n  #11409)。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.27.0 (2026-01-24)\u0009亮点\u0009研磨的新功能","header":"Grind 的其他新功能","id":"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h011"},"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h020":{"contents":"* #11162 减少语言服务器的内存消耗（\n特别是看门狗进程）。在Mathlib中，它减少了内存\n消耗约1GB。* #11164 确保针对未知标识符提供的代码操作\n将 public 和/或 meta 正确插入 module 中* #11577 修复了策略框架报告文件进度条范围\n掩盖了嵌套在策略中的策略块内的进度\n组合器。这是纯粹的视觉变化，增量重新精化\n内部支持的组合器不受影响。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.27.0 (2026-01-24)","header":"Server","id":"/releases/v4.27.0/#zh-releases-v4-27-0-h020"}});